that deliberately
tries to invest

00:37:56.570 --> 00:37:59.950
in energy innovation, green
technology, and so forth.

00:37:59.950 --> 00:38:02.640
So we can also take the
positive side of that

00:38:02.640 --> 00:38:04.225
and maybe run with it a bit.

00:38:04.225 --> 00:38:05.350
KARA MILLER: Question here.

00:38:05.350 --> 00:38:06.140
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:38:06.140 --> 00:38:07.930
Thank you.

00:38:07.930 --> 00:38:09.420
I think your book
captures really

00:38:09.420 --> 00:38:11.170
well the complexity
of the weather system.

00:38:11.170 --> 00:38:12.760
And I think over
the last 50 years

00:38:12.760 --> 00:38:15.230
we've done a great job
of understand really

00:38:15.230 --> 00:38:15.990
complex systems.

00:38:15.990 --> 00:38:18.130
I'd put the world
economy and physiology

00:38:18.130 --> 00:38:20.000
of the human body
in those categories.

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:22.770
And I think what we've
learned is, as much as we know

00:38:22.770 --> 00:38:24.980
about them, we're
still a long way away

00:38:24.980 --> 00:38:28.910
from having the effects that we
want on them in a positive way,

00:38:28.910 --> 00:38:31.000
and truly, deeply
understanding them.

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:33.150
And your book comments
about chaos theory

00:38:33.150 --> 00:38:36.490
being a part of the
challenge with weather.

00:38:36.490 --> 00:38:38.510
I'm just wondering, if
you had a magic wand

00:38:38.510 --> 00:38:41.250
and actually had a technological
solution to greenhouse gases,

00:38:41.250 --> 00:38:45.280
and you therefore weren't
dependent on social change

00:38:45.280 --> 00:38:48.240
and all those effects, and you
also had the political will

00:38:48.240 --> 00:38:50.700
to actually apply
that magic wand,

00:38:50.700 --> 00:38:54.950
I'm wondering whether
we're prepared to have

00:38:54.950 --> 00:38:58.620
that kind of power and
utilize it effectively given

00:38:58.620 --> 00:39:00.760
that changes have all
sorts of uncertain effects

00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:03.630
that we have a very
difficult time dealing with?

00:39:03.630 --> 00:39:05.770
KERRY EMANUEL: That's
a fascinating issue.

00:39:05.770 --> 00:39:08.920
I wish I could give you
a wise answer to that.

00:39:08.920 --> 00:39:10.510
I have always
thought that wisdom

00:39:10.510 --> 00:39:15.980
is the quality of
understanding just

00:39:15.980 --> 00:39:18.640
the depths of your own
ignorance on something.

00:39:18.640 --> 00:39:20.062
And believe me,
climate scientists

00:39:20.062 --> 00:39:22.270
have become very well
acquainted with their ignorance

00:39:22.270 --> 00:39:22.894
on the subject.

00:39:25.570 --> 00:39:28.510
Your question is particularly
pertinent to solutions

00:39:28.510 --> 00:39:31.250
that are on the table and have
been proposed that are broadly

00:39:31.250 --> 00:39:36.380
called geoengineering, in which
we try to compensate for carbon

00:39:36.380 --> 00:39:38.790
dioxide by blocking sunlight.

00:39:38.790 --> 00:39:41.370
And we actually
literally could start

00:39:41.370 --> 00:39:44.180
doing it both technologically
and economically right now.

00:39:44.180 --> 00:39:46.432
We can pump sulphur
to the stratosphere.

00:39:46.432 --> 00:39:47.390
We know how to do that.

00:39:47.390 --> 00:39:49.440
It's not even that expensive.

00:39:49.440 --> 00:39:53.170
But we don't want to
do that because we're

00:39:53.170 --> 00:39:56.260
so familiar with our ignorance,
if you will, of the system

00:39:56.260 --> 00:40:00.060
that we can give a pretty good
estimate what will happen.

00:40:00.060 --> 00:40:03.580
But we wouldn't be too
surprised if we were wrong.

00:40:03.580 --> 00:40:05.430
So there's all sorts of things.

00:40:05.430 --> 00:40:08.290
If I had a magic
wand right now, I

00:40:08.290 --> 00:40:10.540
would implement a
stiff carbon tax

00:40:10.540 --> 00:40:14.220
and let the market, science,
engineering kind of work

00:40:14.220 --> 00:40:17.140
it out, because I think
we're so close to being

00:40:17.140 --> 00:40:20.700
able to pull carbon back out
of the atmosphere, which is not

00:40:20.700 --> 00:40:23.490
so dangerous, because
we're just reversing damage

00:40:23.490 --> 00:40:25.720
that we've already done.

00:40:25.720 --> 00:40:27.510
KARA MILLER: Question here.

